Event Instructions

Set Up


Guest Arrival


Welcome

- First Rule of CopterCross: Breath.
- Second Rule of CopterCross: Be Gentle and Slow.. 
- Third Rule of CopterCross: Throttle down if you lose control

1) Partner Up
   Instructions for how Pilot/Co-Pilot teams work together:
   Co-Pilot reads instructions and acts as a second set of eyes.
   Pilot flies Copter.

   Find a buddy team!
   These are your go-to people for questions, problems etc. 
   Plus, during the main event, they are going to be your partners in the relay race.

2) Safety
   blades are sharp!
   rotor guards
   picking up a copter
      1) communication with pilot 
        P: Good to Grab!
        CP: Grabbing! 
      2) how to pick up a Copter without hurting it or yourself

3) Batteries (and battery maintenance)
   Include Battery Practice
   + Battery cheat sheet
   cheat sheet should include voice commands (a la rock climbing) such as:
   *Charging!*
   *Green Bag*
   *Red Bag*

   as well as instructions for "batteries that have been used (at all) go in the red bag" and "Fully charged batteries go in the green bag"

4) Language!
     Fun Drills for pilot/co-pilot communication
     Flash cards?
     Design a game?
     Map words to motion?
     Map words to controls?
     Map controls to motion?
yaw-	rotating right or left
pitch- forward and backward
roll-	right and left
uplift- fly up
downfall- fly down

5) Be the Copter
       Pilot / Co-Pilot practice
       builds intuitive understanding of copter movements
       reinforces language lessons

6) Crawling
    Rotating on the ground, without leaving the ground.

7) Baby Steps
    Take off, reach 3 inches, hover, land.  Repeat 3 times.
    switch

    Take off, reach 6 inches, hover, land.  Repeat 3 times.
    switch

    Take off, reach 1 foot, hover, land.  Repeat 3 times.
    switch

    Take off, reach 3 feet, hover, land.  Repeat 3 times.
    switch

    Take off, reach 6 feet, hover, land.  Repeat 3 times.
    switch

    Take off, reach 6 feet, hover, 
            then to 3 feet, hover, 
            then to 1 foot, hover,
            then to 6 inches, hover,
            then to 3 inches, hover,
            Land
    switch

8) Walking Forward & Backward
    Take off, 
    hover at 3 feet.
    Fly forward 5 feet.
    hover.
    fly backward to origin.
    hover.
    land.

    switch

9) Walking Sideways
    Take off, 
    hover at 3 feet.
    Fly left 5 feet.
    hover.
    fly right to origin.
    hover.
    fly right 5 feet.
    hover.
    fly left to origin.
    hover.
    land.

    Repeat 3 times.

    switch

10) Rotating

   Take off
   Rotate to 10 o'clock
   Fly forward and back to the origin.
   Hover
   Take off
   Rotate to 2 o'clock
   
   Repeat 3 times
   
   switch
  
11) Nose-In Walking Forward and Backward (Hard)
   Face nose towards pilot. 
      Right will be left. Backwards will be forwards
      Like balancing a stick. Whatever direction quad goes, stick goes
   
   Take off, 
      hover at 3 feet.
    Fly forward 5 feet.
    hover.
    fly backward to origin.
    hover.
    land.

Repeat 3 times

    switch

11) Nose-In Walking Side-to-Side (Hard)
   Face nose towards pilot. 
      Right will be left. Backwards will be forwards
      Like balancing a stick. Whatever direction quad goes, stick goes
      
    Take off, 
    hover at 3 feet.
    Fly left 5 feet.
    hover.
    fly right to origin.
    hover.
    fly right 5 feet.
    hover.
    fly left to origin.
    hover.
    land.

    Repeat 3 times.

    switch

13) Walking with Scissors: Banking
   Start going forward, about 5 mph
   Apply small amount of aileron.
   Continuously pull up on elevator
   Continuously apply yaw. 

14) Walking with Scissors: Figure 8's

15) Walking with Scissors: Flips

16) Fly by Screen
    Pilot / Co-Pilot collaboration
    walk through the initial babysteps list, but with your back turned.  Co-pilot has visual on copter.  Co-pilot gives verbal confirmation on height and location of copter.  CO-PILOT: BE VERY VERBAL.  YOU ARE THE PILOT'S EYES ON THIS ONE. 

17) Mini-Obstacle Course Test Runs

18) Style And Flair (expression session?)

19) Snap a pic!

20) The Main Event!






